document:
## Key Changes from Previous FAS Version

The key areas updated are:

*   **Title and Scope:** The standard's title and scope were modified to specifically focus on diminishing Musharaka real estate funds structured as a *shirkah al-ʿaqd*.
*   **Definitions:** New definitions were added for 'Shirkah al-ʿAqd', 'Fair Market Value', and 'Non-cash contribution'.
*   **Non-Cash Contributions:** Specific guidance was added for the recognition and initial measurement of non-cash contributions (FAS4.DM.ACC1 and FAS4.SH1).
*   **Partner Exits:** Specific guidance was added for the accounting treatment of partner exits (FAS4.DM.ACC2 and FAS4.SH2).
*   **Disclosure Requirements:** The disclosure requirements were expanded to include more specific details related to diminishing Musharaka real estate funds.

These updates address gaps in the previous version of FAS 4 and ensure Shariah compliance and consistency in accounting practices.

{
  "pages": [
    {
      "title": "Title & Effective Date",
      "content": {
        "standard_number": "FAS 4 (Revised 2024)",
        "title": "Accounting for Investments in Diminishing Musharaka Real Estate Funds (Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd)",
        "example_title": "Accounting for Innovative Digital Assets",
        "effective_date": "31 December 2024 (Gregorian) / 19 Jumada II 1446 (Hijri)",
        "issued_by": "AI-Driven Standard Enhancement System (Conceptual)"
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Objective, Scope & Key Principles",
      "content": {
        "objective": [
          "To provide specific accounting guidance for investments in diminishing Musharaka real estate funds structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd, particularly addressing the valuation of non-cash contributions and the accounting treatment of partner exits.",
          "This standard clarifies the application of FAS 4 in the context of diminishing Musharaka, ensuring Shariah compliance and consistent accounting practices."
        ],
        "scope": {
          "applicable_transactions_entities": "This standard applies to Islamic financial institutions and other entities that invest in diminishing Musharaka real estate funds structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd.",
          "exclusions": "This standard does not cover diminishing Musharaka arrangements outside the scope of real estate funds or those not structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd."
        },
        "key_shariah_principles": [
          "Fair valuation of assets at the time of contribution.",
          "Adherence to agreed-upon profit-sharing ratios.",
          "Prohibition of riba (interest) and excessive gharar (uncertainty).",
          "Transparency and full disclosure of material information."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Definitions",
      "content": {
        "definitions": [
          {
            "term": "Diminishing Musharaka",
            "definition": "A form of partnership where one partner gradually transfers their share in the asset to the other partner over time."
          },
          {
            "term": "Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd",
            "definition": "A contractual partnership."
          },
          {
            "term": "Fair Market Value",
            "definition": "The price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date."
          },
          {
            "term": "Non-cash contribution",
            "definition": "Contribution to a partnership in the form of assets other than cash, such as land, property, or development rights."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Recognition and Initial Measurement",
      "content": {
        "recognition": {
          "general_criteria": "An investment in a diminishing Musharaka real estate fund structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd shall be recognized when the entity becomes a party to the musharaka agreement and obtains rights and obligations arising from the agreement.",
          "specific_points": "Non-cash contributions from partners shall be recognized at the date of contribution, provided that a reliable fair value can be determined."
        },
        "initial_measurement": {
          "general_principle": "Investments in diminishing Musharaka real estate funds shall be initially measured at fair market value.",
          "specific_guidance": "Non-cash contributions shall be initially measured at their fair market value at the date of contribution, as determined by a qualified, independent valuation expert acceptable to the Shariah advisor. Any costs directly attributable to the contribution shall be added to the initial carrying amount of the investment."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Subsequent Measurement & De-recognition",
      "content": {
        "subsequent_measurement": {
          "measurement_basis": "The investment should be measured based on the applicable measurement basis as prescribed by FAS 4 and other relevant standards.",
          "changes_in_value": "Changes in the value of the investment are recognized in accordance with FAS 4.",
          "profit_loss_recognition": "Profit or loss should be allocated according to the agreed-upon profit-sharing ratio stipulated in the musharaka agreement at the formation of the contract, provided it is free from riba and excessive gharar."
        },
        "de_recognition": {
          "criteria": "An investment in a diminishing Musharaka real estate fund should be de-recognized when the entity relinquishes control over the investment, typically upon sale or liquidation of the investment.",
          "accounting": "Upon a partner's exit from a diminishing Musharaka real estate fund structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd before its maturity, the difference between the carrying amount of the exiting partner's investment and the consideration received, net of any directly attributable transaction costs, shall be recognized as a profit or loss in the period of exit. This profit or loss shall be allocated among the remaining partners and the exiting partner (if applicable) according to the agreed-upon profit-sharing ratio."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Disclosure Requirements",
      "content": {
        "qualitative_disclosures": [
          "Description of the nature of diminishing Musharaka real estate funds and the entity's investment therein.",
          "Key accounting policies adopted for measuring and recognizing the investment.",
          "Information about risk management practices related to the investment.",
          "Shari'ah compliance aspects of the diminishing Musharaka arrangement, including the role of the Shariah advisor.",
          "The method of determining the consideration received upon partner exit, the allocation of profit or loss, and any related Shariah pronouncements shall be disclosed."
        ],
        "quantitative_disclosures": [
          "Breakdown of the carrying amount of the investment.",
          "Reconciliation of movements in the carrying amount of the investment.",
          "Income and expenses recognized from the investment.",
          "Maturity analysis of the investment (if applicable).",
          "Information on any impaired assets or provisions related to the investment."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Basis for Conclusions (Summary)",
      "content": {
        "rationale": "This standard provides specific guidance for the accounting treatment of investments in diminishing Musharaka real estate funds structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd, addressing gaps in existing FAS 4 regarding the valuation of non-cash contributions and the accounting for partner exits. It promotes consistent accounting practices and enhances the reliability of financial reporting.",
        "shariah_compliance": "The standard ensures alignment with Shari'ah principles by requiring fair valuation of assets, adherence to agreed-upon profit-sharing ratios, and transparency in accounting and disclosure. It emphasizes the role of the Shariah advisor in ensuring compliance.",
        "addressing_gaps": "This standard specifically addresses the user context by providing clarity on how to account for partner contributions and exits in diminishing Musharaka real estate funds structured as a shirkah al-\u02bfaqd, which were previously areas of uncertainty under FAS 4."
      }
    }
  ]
}
